node.text: Upon formal completion of a buyout with the Detroit Pistons, center DeAndre Jordan intends to sign with the Los Angeles Lakers, sources tell ESPN. Jordan would have to first clear waivers to become a free agent.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on September 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEM Adrian Wojnarowski @wojespn After retiring with heart concerns five months ago, seven-time All-Star forward LaMarcus Aldridge is returning on a one-year, $2.6 million deal with the Brooklyn Nets, his agent Jeff Schwartz of @excelbasketball tells ESPN.'.

node.text: Aldridge, 36, has been medically cleared by a number of doctors – including those both independent and Nets-affiliated – to make a return for his 16th season, Schwartz told ESPN

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on September 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'infor BED-STLM STLM Adrian Wojnarowski @wojespn ESPN Sources: Brooklyn is trading c DeAndre Jordan, four future-second round picks and $5.78M to Detroit for Jahlil Okafor and Sekou Doumbouya. Pistons plan to work through a buyout on two-years, $20M owed Jordan; Nets will save $47M in salary and tax on deal.'.

node.text:
Pistons plan to work on the buyout with Jordan to allow him to become a free agent, per sources. In that scenario, the Lakers are expected to be a serious contender, per sources. 
Nets send Pistons their own 2022 and 2027 second-round picks, a 2024 second-rounder via Wizards and a 2025 second via Warriors, sources tell ESPN.
Nets have shown ability to recruit top-level vet-minimum talent as a big-market title contender, which alleviates pressure of surrendering picks over life of Durant/Harden/Irving era. $47M in savings can be reinvested into free agents at mid-level exception, buying future seconds.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on September 03, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people playing sports, indoor and text that says 'MINNESOTA 41 ENTER'.

node.text:
Memphis has agreed to trade forward Juancho Hernangomez to Boston for guards Kris Dunn, Carsen Edwards and a 2026 second-round pick swap, sources tell ESPN.

Deal can’t be completed until September 15, when Dunn and Edwards contracts are allowed to be aggregated in the trade.

Hernangomez gives the Celtics another potential floor-spacer in a bench role; Grizzlies continue to find some value in margins and will continue to be open to deals as franchise manages a roster numbers crunch ahead of 2021-2022 season.

node.text: @atlhawks center @ccapela15 has agreed on a two-year, $46 million contract  extension, sources tell ESPN. He had two years, $36M left on his current deal and now is under contract through 2024-2025.

node.text: Rajon Rondo plans to sign a one-year, $2.6M deal with the Lakers upon clearing waivers today, sources tell ESPN. He agreed to a contract buyout with Memphis on Saturday. Rondo will still make his full $7.5M salary this season between buyout and new deal.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 28, 2021 tagging @lakers, @bdasports, and @rajonrondo. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'LAKERS wish Adrian Wojnarowski @wojespn After agreeing to a buyout with the Memphis Grizzlies, the Los Angeles Lakers are the frontrunners to sign guard Rajon Rondo, sources tell ESPN.'.

node.text: Rondo will likely sign with the Lakers after clearing waivers on Monday, per sources. Rondo was a part of the franchise’s 2020 NBA title in The Bubble.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 28, 2021 tagging @cavs, @kevinlove, and @excelbasketball. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
Five-time All-Star forward @kevinlove has no interest in negotiating a buyout on the two years, $60 million left on his contract with the Cleveland Cavaliers, his agent Jeff Schwartz of @excelbasketball told ESPN on Saturday.
“There have been no talks with Cleveland on a buyout, nor is there any interest from Kevin in doing a buyout," Schwartz told ESPN.
The Cavaliers have periodically explored trading Love -- a scenario that he's supports -- but have been unable to find a deal that they're willing to execute, sources said.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'ZENAY Adrian Wojnarowski @wojespn Cleveland is acquiring Chicago restricted free agent F Lauri Markkanen on a four-year, $67M deal in a sign-and-trade, sources tell ESPN.'.

node.text: ESPN Sources: Cleveland’s acquiring Chicago’s Lauri Markkanen in three-way sign and trade with Portland. Bulls get Derrick Jones Jr., POR’s 2022 lottery protected future 1st and Cavs’ 2023 second-round pick via Denver. Portland gets forward Larry Nance Jr.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 24, 2021. May be an image of 5 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
After leading the @bucks to the franchise’s first NBA championship in 50 years, coach Mike Budenholzer has agreed on a three-year contract extension, sources tell ESPN.
Budenholzer – a two-time coach of the year who had been entering the final year of his deal --- now ties himself to the Bucks through the 2024-2025 season.
